  "content": "### Task 1.1: Extend `EntryMetadata` with new fields\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test -p corvia-common test_entry_metadata_new_fields -- --nocapture`\nExpected: FAIL — `content_role` and `source_origin` fields don't exist on `EntryMetadata`\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Add fields to `EntryMetadata`**\n\nIn `types.rs`, add to the `EntryMetadata` struct after `end_line`:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq, Default)]\npub struct EntryMetadata {\n    pub source_file: Option<String>,\n    pub language: Option<String>,\n    pub chunk_type: Option<String>,\n    pub start_line: Option<u32>,\n    pub end_line: Option<u32>,\n    #[serde(default)]\n    pub content_role: Option<String>,\n    #[serde(default)]\n    pub source_origin: Option<String>,\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run test to verify it passes**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test -p corvia-common test_entry_metadata_new_fields -- --nocapture`\nExpected: PASS\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Run full corvia-common tests to verify no regressions**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test -p corvia-common`\nExpected: All tests pass. Existing serialization tests still work because `#[serde(default)]` makes new fields optional.\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-common/src/types.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(common): add content_role and source_origin to EntryMetadata\"\n```\n\n---\n",
